---
description: Keep every rendered web string in plain handler-facing language
globs: apps/web/**/*.{tsx,ts}
alwaysApply: false
---

# UI user language

The web app is for case handlers. Render only terms they recognize from their
work and describe actions from their point of view.

Never expose infrastructure, authentication, storage, configuration, transport,
schema, development, deployment, test-data, specification, or internal lifecycle
terminology in labels, headings, buttons, toasts, tooltips, placeholders,
validation messages, badges, or empty states.

Keep domain words such as EVA, registration, Case/PO, Principal, work provider,
claimant, inspection, chaser, photo, evidence, and queue. If a feature is
unavailable, say what the handler cannot do and what they can do next.
